[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Considering test resources**\n\nI'm thinking about adding a test resource called reflect-config for the org.apache.tools.ant.Project, specifically to register allDeclaredConstructors. This is solely test-only metadata and can make the class more active. Initializing Project.class will let me get those constructors and create instances. But, hmm, will adding this metadata affect the report since it’s not an active class? I could also consider using initializeClass for Path.class. It seems like JUnit might have reflection metadata for its test class constructors, but user filters might exclude it.\n\n**Exploring class loading issues**\n\nI'm thinking about how to instantiate a custom-loaded class, but it seems like reflection is prohibited. I wonder if using Ant's Project.createClassLoader would help, but that doesn't seem like an option either. Maybe I could try calling AntClassLoader.class.getClassLoader().loadClass(\"org.apache.tools.ant.AntClassLoader\"). However, it looks like that won't reinitialize the class properly. I'm also hitting a wall with resetting synthetic static fields, as this requires reflection. It's a bit frustrating!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_09f14628d302d2430169efc55c8ea4819cb67b138057b08346\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp78VsWSYqmK9Z4uq-gdlbK0Dufn6_9ATXj9lVYGIRcEA5JI9i-gBQLX32Vh97Q-RQfpN9b-sfE5i_sCMn2y3K0Wl1KJABUB_YBPMvfiKmuOLpTZT3xUhgeowdXqSNz8OMUmCdo7EmKnk6HfPFk7J0ojuK2Kw2rHra0GOkMHFilrubaXfz4nziINpGaEA4-n3VwStz9zsqWl1hmFMxMrhZnv5AaReCG6kgn0kauAOQIs9EGjGOOElzN62LHmjT64KxcHJ19siB-_gWfHsy79Q7MBi6AfxVY7O-FSm33G-uxPyoPJLLehHzFFu_Mq2uEqa76WptiLqy5Gpz8sMntFRQYStxHh_sX-5o7uR-pc0zeRvMNDG2dAbLNaqJ7XwHsw3EzHg3mMfVb3SdnlnZVhFMgMhw6dufbipJ21hOQTwUwSYloKqXURCHRwpl8eTA660el7KhRTy7b8fUMgAtqKmJsbxdRtKkVuvuFwTWEq24JfigXOSOG52FJtTbeEFVTZNglTj2i_n50xBhQIJPMkw1z8MhHRkmRUH01O72mfnC-my_ZDsarxIEM_WCaBu07VoYPTudqJYA0kS